The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, June 28: The cabinet is likely to take up tomorrow the issue of granting an extension of four months to the department of telecom (DoT) to implement the revised guidelines for foreign direct investment in the telecom sector. The DoT is sorting out some of the security-related issues, while implementing the enhanced FDI of 74 per cent from 49 per cent. The issue of FDI in telecom has become a tug-of-war between the National Security Council (NSC) and the DoT and various issues still need to be resolved, sources said.

 New Delhi, June 28: Prime Minister Manmohan Singh has asked finance ministers to consider bringing debt-ridden handloom weavers within the ambit of low-interest loans that are provided to farmers, and he expects the problem to be resolved in the next three months. 

 Calcutta, June 28: The Steel Authority of India (SAIL) has approved the expansion of Salem Steel Plant in Tamil Nadu at an investment of Rs 1,553 crore. Under the plan, a facility will be installed to produce 180,000 tonnes of stainless steel slabs per annum and the plant?s cold rolling capacity will be raised from 65,000 to 146,000 tonnes. 

 New Delhi, June 28: The Cellular Operators? Association of India (COAI) has accused CDMA players of spreading misinformation about the spectrum policy by claiming it is biased towards GSM operators.




